If you are looking for an epic brunch item that is super easy to make and budget-friendly – try the Corned Beef Hash recipe below featuring PALM Corned Beef.
 
PALM Corned Beef is currently offered in 6 different flavours, is imported from New Zealand, and is made using grass fed/free-range beef. All of their shredded brisket-styled corned beef is super easy to prepare, ready to eat and all have the same juicy and savory flavour.
 
Follow along below, and you will have breakfast in under 25 minutes
 
Ingredients:
·  4 tablespoons butter 
·  Onions, diced into cubes
·  2 Cans of PALM Corned Beef
·  3 cups of diced potato
·  1 green pepper 
·  Eggs
·  Green Onions
·  Chili Peppers
·  Sesame Seeds for garnish
·  fresh parsley for garnish chopped
 
Directions:
1.  Melt butter in a cast iron skillet over medium-high heat.
2.  Add onion and sauté for 3 minutes.
3.  Add cooked potatoes and mix together with onions for another 5 minutes.
4.  Add in canned Corned Beef and mix together gently for another few mins and close the lid to allow the potatoes to fully cook. Once all items start to brown, you can remove them in two minutes.
5.  In another pan cook eggs sunny side up or to your liking.
6.  Remove from stovetop and garnish with eggs, green onions, chili peppers and eggs.

Ingredients

·      8 egg yolks (locally sourced)
·      1/2 cup locally sourced maple sugar 
·      1 cup heavy whipping cream (locally sourced)
·      2 cup milk (locally sourced) 
·      1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract 
·      1/2 teaspoon nutmeg
·      1/8 teaspoon clove
·      1/8 teaspoon allspice
·      1/8 teaspoon cinnamon
·      Pinch of salt
·      1/4 cup Diplomático Reserva Exclusiva

Recipe

·      Whisk egg yolks and sugar until homogeneous 
·      Over medium heat mix cream, milk, spices and salt, mix until low simmer
·      Slowly add simmering milk mixture to room temp egg mixture to temper eggs whisking thoroughly throughout 
·      Once both solutions are combined add back to low heat and whisk constantly for 2-4 minutes until ideal texture is achieved
·      Remove from heat, add vanilla and Diplomático Reserva Exclusiva

Over the holidays, we got some time to perfect our Winter and holiday recipes on my @BrevilleCanada – Joule Oven Air Fryer Pro.  This smart oven’s built in Element IQ system allows for versatility in making an abundance of different dishes!  The ability to control the temperature and to turn off the oven from a simple touch of your phone also makes things way easier especially during the busy holiday season.  The Joule App also comes loaded with several amazing recipes for any home cook to try!

Featured above is our homemade Focaccia which we finally perfected!

Rosemary Garlic Focaccia

Ingredients

600g all purpose flour
450g warm water
6g course salt
2tbsp extra virgin olive oil
¼ tsp active yeast 
A large head of confit garlic
Fresh rosemary
Kalamata olives

Directions

Combine all purpose flour and yeast in large bowl and mix thoroughly
In a separate bowl, add salt to the warm water and mix until salt is fully dissolved
Add and mix water and extra virgin olive oil into bowl with flour and yeast
Transfer dough to another lightly greased mixing bowl
Coil fold the dough (repeat 4 times in 20 minute increments)
Cover the bowl with a damp towel and let the dough rise until dough doubles
Gently stretch and press dough and let rest for two hours
Top your dough with confit garlic, olives, and roasted garlic, and drizzle extra oil on top of dough
Bake in @BrevilleCanada Joule Oven Air Fryer Pro for 450 degree F for 15-20 mins

Looking to entertain guests anytime soon, this pull-apart Garlic Cheese Loaf will be your new crowd favourite!  This dish is super easy to make and does not require many ingredients. The most important part is the loaf of bread and of course the CHEESE! 
 
Ingredients 
Uncut Loaf of bread – Ciabatta 
Armstrong Ontario Cheese 
Balderson Aged Cheddar 
1 Stick of Garlic Butter 
Chopped Garlic 
1 tsp Salt 
½ tsp Italian Seasoning 

Instructions: 
Preheat oven to 375F 
Combine chopped garlic and garlic butter in bowl and microwave until butter is melted. 
Shred cheese into a bowl 
Cut bread diagonally at about 3 cm intervals (Make sure to not cut all the way through, approx. 80% depth) 
Pry open all the open cracks and generously place melted butter and cheese evenly across the loaf 
Brush the surface of the bread with melted butter and season with Italian Seasoning 
Bake for 15 mins with loaf wrapped in tinfoil and 10 more mins unwrapped to give the bread colour and to allow cheese to fully melt.

Looking to make something exciting for your next dinner party? This Cheesy Hash Brown Casserole made with the finest Ontario Cheese will definitely win over even the pickiest of eaters.  This mouth-watering and flavourful dish can be easily prepped in just 15 mins and cooked in under an hour!

Ingredients:

1 (1.2 kg) package frozen hash brown potatoes, thawed

2 cups shredded marble cheese

1 cup shredded sharp cheddar cheese 

1 can condensed cream of chicken soup

1 (8 ounce) container sour cream

¾ cup butter, melted 

½ cup chopped onion

4 cloves garlic minced 

Salt and pepper to taste 

Cooking Instructions:

Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. 

Combine hash browns, marble cheese, condensed soup, sour cream, melted butter, onion, garlic, salt, and pepper in a large bowl.

Transfer mixture to a pre-greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover casserole and bake in the preheated oven for 50 minutes.

Looking for a game day appetizer that will impress the pickiest of crowds! This Aged Cheddar Sausage Popper Cheese Boat will surely become the new crowd favourite at your next event.  You’ll want to make sure to get that perfect aged cheddar cheese as it is the perfect match to bring out all the flavours from the savoury sausages, mild cream cheese and spicy jalapenos!  
 
Ingredients:
 
One Package of fresh sausages (6 – 8 Sausages – Do not use frozen or fully cooked sausages as it is hard to score the casing of the sausage
One Block of Balderson Aged Cheddar Cheese
Sour Cream
Jalapeños Peppers
Cream Cheese
 
Instructions:
Place sausages on a flat surface and score the middle of the casing on the sausages towards the ends
Gently pull apart and open the middle of the sausage and form an opening towards the center of the sausage
Fill a small block approx. 1 table spoon of cream cheese into the middle of the sausage
Gently place a few jalapeños on top of the cream cheese 
Grate Ontario Aged Cheddar Cheese and apply generously on top of sausages
Set oven to 300° and bake time is 40-45 minutes

Both comfort recipes feature an abundance of local Ontario dairy products including milk and cheese!  Remember the more cheese you add the more epic your pull will be!  Both dishes are perfect compliments to each other and can be made in under 25 minutes!
 
Cheesy Corn Ingredients:
1.5 cups Corn
1 cup local Ontario Marble Cheese, shredded
1 tsp sugar
1/3 cup Green Onions, chopped
Salt and pepper to taste
100 ML of local Ontario Milk
1/3 cup local Ontario Cream Cheese
 
Cheesy Corn Instructions:
Preheat Oven to 400 ˚F.
Combine all ingredients above into mixing bowl and stir
Pour mixed items into a baking dish
Apply additional layer of cheese on top
Bake for ten minutes and enjoy!
 
Cheesy Ramen Ingredients:
3 Pack of Ramen
1 Cup of local Ontario Marble Cheese, shredded
2 Cups of local Ontario Milk
½ Cup of local Ontario Butter
2 Stocks Green Onion
3 Cloves of Garlic
Sesame Seeds 
 
Cheesy Ramen Instructions:
Boil water and cook ramen until al dente
In separate pan, sauté garlic until fragrant and in cheese and milk. Stir until cheese is fully melted.
Pour the cheese sauce into an oven safe dish, add in cooked ramen and mix until sauce is incorporated
Top with a layer of cheese and broil in oven for 7 minutes
Garnish with green onions and sesame seeds

The best kind of comfort food in under 30 minutes.  This exciting Crispy Cheesy Beef Tacos featuring the best of Ontario Dairy Products including cheese and milk is always a family favourite.  To take your meal to the next level, you can also add the Creamy Cheese Dip (Recipe also shown below) for the perfect gooey cheese dunk!
 
Ingredients: 
500 G of Ground Beef
Taco Seasoning
2 Cup of Ontario Marble Cheese
1 Cup of Onions, Diced
Flour Tortillas
1 cup of local Ontario Whole Milk 
1/2 Cup of Ontario Butter
1 Diced Tomato
1 Avocado 
 
Steps:
In a heated pan, add ground beef, taco seasoning and chopped onions and cook for 8 minutes.
In another sauce pan melt butter, then add in shredded cheese and milk. Stir mixture until evenly combined.
Add a sprinkle of shredded cheese onto another heated non-stick pan on medium heat in a circular shape, after 1 minute place tortilla shell onto cheese.
Consistently check the bottom of the tortilla shell until cheese crust is golden brown.
Assemble the tacos by placing beef mixture into the cheesy crusted tortilla shells and add desired toppings like tomato and avocado.
Dip or drizzle cheese sauce on top and enjoy!
